[{"id":"VH903495","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a Lewis diagram. There is a Nitrogen atom bonded to three Oxygen atoms, two of them with single bonds and one with a double bond. The oxygen atoms connected with single bonds each have three nonbonding pairs of electrons. The oxygen atom connected with a double bond has two nonbonding pairs of electrons. The diagram is contained in brackets, with a negative sign to its upper right.\" height=\"76\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH903495.g03.png\" width=\"120\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following statements, if true, would support the claim that the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N O 3 minus\"><math alttext=\"N O 3 minus\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>NO</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ion, represented above, has three resonance structures?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH903495_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N O 3 minus\"><math alttext=\"N O 3 minus\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>NO</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ion is not a polar species.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The oxygen-to-nitrogen-to-oxygen bond angles are <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"90 degrees\"><math alttext=\"90 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>90</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">One of the bonds in <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N O 3 minus\"><math alttext=\"N O 3 minus\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>NO</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is longer than the other two.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">One of the bonds in <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N O 3 minus\"><math alttext=\"N O 3 minus\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msup><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>NO</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is shorter than the other two.</p>"],"answer":0}]